# Conventional Commits

When generating commit messages, use the Conventional Commits format.

## Format

```
<type>(<scope>): <short description>

[optional body - explain what and why]
```

## Types

| Type | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `feat` | New feature |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `docs` | Documentation only |
| `style` | Code style (formatting, no logic change) |
| `refactor` | Code refactoring (no feature/fix) |
| `perf` | Performance improvement |
| `test` | Adding/fixing tests |
| `chore` | Build, CI, dependencies |
| `build` | Build system changes |
| `ci` | CI configuration |

## Rules

- **Description**: lowercase, no period, imperative mood ("add" not "added")
- **Scope**: optional, indicates affected area (e.g., `auth`, `inventory`, `api`)
- **Body**: optional, explains motivation for change
- **Length**: subject line max 72 characters

## Examples

```
feat(inventory): add product catalog autocomplete search

Allows users to search the product_catalog when adding items via
the QuickAddSheet. Auto-selects default unit from catalog products.
```

```
fix(auth): resolve session expiration redirect loop
```

```
refactor(api): extract validation into reusable middleware
```

```
chore(deps): update shadcn/ui components
```
